Evaluate “Organization as a Service” in Grafana Enterprise

Task goal

Evaluate the option of providing Grafana Organization as a Service through our internal platform America.

In this model, a client uses America to create a new Grafana organization, and from that point can manage their own space independently: add users, grant access, create dashboards, folders, alerts, teams, and manage their own day-to-day Grafana usage within the boundaries we define.

The purpose of this task is not to implement the solution yet, but to produce a clear evaluation of whether this is the right operating model for us.

What you need to examine

You need to analyze this service model from a platform point of view and explain:
	•	what are the main advantages of giving customers their own Grafana organization through America
	•	what are the main disadvantages
	•	what are the limitations of this model
	•	what stays under platform team responsibility even if the customer gets their own organization
	•	what the customer can truly manage alone, and what they still cannot do
	•	what are the operational, governance, security, and scale risks
	•	in which cases this model is a good fit, and in which cases it is not

Main questions this task must answer

Your output should give clear answers to the following:
	1.	What do we gain by giving each client their own Grafana organization?
	2.	What problems can this create for us as the platform owner?
	3.	Does this model create real isolation, or only partial isolation?
	4.	What dependencies on the central platform team still remain?
	5.	What can become difficult when the number of organizations grows?
	6.	What governance rules would likely be needed for this to work well?
	7.	What are the main reasons to choose this model, and what are the main reasons not to?

Scope

Focus specifically on the model of:
	•	one shared Grafana Enterprise platform
	•	multiple client organizations
	•	self-service org creation through America
	•	customers managing their own organization after creation

Do not go deep into alternative architectures such as full dedicated Grafana per customer, unless it is needed briefly for comparison.

Do not design the full implementation in this task.
